0 WAR STARTWAR ENDWAR WARSTATS JOINWAR ELIMINATE~
There are two types of War:

          1. Last Man Standing:   Basically, this war goes on until
                                  there is only one person remaining.
                                  Players receive a reward for each
                                  person eliminated, and the winner
                                  gets a bonus.

          2. Team Deathmatch:     Two teams duke it out in the style
                                  of Last Man Standing. Players are
                                  divided between two teams, and the
                                  team that survives the war wins.

To join a war, type '#wJoinWar#n' when an immortal starts the countdown.
For an immortal to start the countdown, he or she must use the '#wStartWar#n' command.
There is also an '#wEndWar#n' command, which ends the war immediately.
To see the syntax of the StartWar command, type StartWar (Immortals Only)
To see the current war status, type '#wwarstats#n'.
Once in a war you may defeat others with the '#wEliminate#n' command.

War Code ©2001 Malawar
http://www.malawar.net/mudding
Further changes by Kyrlin.
~

