0 MONK MONKS~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Monks are servants of God. They are masters of the body and spirit.
Defensive in nature, a monk spends his or her life practicing the mystical
arts. God grants monks special abilities that allow them to compete with the
evil Supernatual creatures they aim to smite.

#0[#7*#0]#n Favour      -  This command is for inducting/outcasting & promoting.
#0[#7*#0]#n Fightstyle  -  This command sets your fighting style.
#0[#7*#0]#n Guide       -  This command is for guiding monks into your class.
#0[#7*#0]#n Learn       -  This command allows Monks to gain their powers.
#0[#7*#0]#n Meditate    -  Regain health faster.
#0[#7*#0]#n Monktalk    -  Monk only communication channel.
#0[#7*#0]#n Upkeep      -  This command shows what powers you currantly have.

Also see help: #wMONKABILITIES#n, #wMONKCHI#n, #wMONKBLOCK#n, #wMONKCOMBO#n, #wMONKFOCUS#n,
#wMONKCOUNTER#n, #wFIGHTSTYLE#n.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 MONKCHI~

A monk's chi is the essential part of combat.  The higher
the monk's chi, the better he or she can parry and dodge
blows.  It also gives the monk more strength and power,
thus letting him or her inflict more damage and receive
less.  Maintaining chi is very strenuous, and requires
that the monk have plenty of vitality.
~

0 MONKCOMBO~

By using his or her special techniques, such as thrust kick,
in a certain order, he or she may perform special combos.
Each combo has a different effect.  Some may do damage to the
victim, some syphon movement points, and some may stun the victim.
A monk's combos are a very mysterious thing, thus the monk
must spend much of his or her life trying to perfect
these combos.
~

0 MONKBLOCK~

A monk's block counter allows him to parry blows much better.
This counter increments whenever a monk parries a blow.
The max block counter is 150, and the higher it gets, the
better the monk parries.  After the fight stops, the block
counter will soon reset to 0.
~

0 MONKFOCUS~

Elite monks have the ability to focus the power of God
into his or her own special attacks.  After a monk has
gained focus points, he or she must use them to perform
special attacks that have devastating effects.  The only
downside to these attacks is that it takes a monk a
very long time to recover the focus required to do such
extraordinary feats.
~

0 MONKABILITIES~
Monks have four special abilities granted to them by God.
Each ability has four levels, which cost 500k exp each.
For more info on the Abilities,
See Help: 'MONKSPIRIT' 'MONKCOMBAT' 'MONKBODY' and 'MONKAWARENESS'
~

0 MONKSPIRIT~

Level 1 - Blinding Agony. This power allows the monk to hurl
a ball of pure evil at a foe.  It blinds the foe, and prevents
him or her to flee or recall.

Level 2 - Natural Harmony (auto).  This power allows the monk to
absorb the evil of someone who attacks him or her and channel
them into energy, which heals the Monk.

Level 3 - Healing Touch.  This power allows the monk to imbue his
target with the essence of God, healing his or her wounds.

Level 4 - Death Touch. This power allows the monk to give his victim a
deadly disease which cripples and wounds him or her.
~

0 MONKAWARENESS~

Level 1 - Nightsight

Level 2 - Shadowsight

Level 3 - Truesight

Level 4 - Scry
~

0 MONKBODY~

Level 1 - Adamantium Hands.  This power allows the monk's hands to become
incredibly hard, like adamantium.  This allows the monk to do more damage
and parry blows with his or her bare hands.

Level 2 - Body of Stone (Auto).  At this mastery of the body, the monk's
body is as hard as a stone, causing him or her to take reduced damage.

Level 3 - Spiritpower.  This power allows the monk to channel his or her
energy into offensive attacks, significantly raising his or her hitroll
and damroll.

Level 4 - The Glow (Auto).  Only a true master of the body has this
ability.  The monk's power is so great that his or her hands glow
brightly with the power of God and the monk's holy spirit.  The 
effect of this glow is varied, but often dangerous.
~

0 MONKCOMBAT~

This ability improves the monk's combat ability per level.
Each level gives the monk more knowledge of combat,
allowing him or her to do more damage, hit more often, and
parry and dodge more.
~

0 MONKCOUNTER~

The monk's block counter is a very important part of a monk's blocking.
The block counter increases everytime a monk parries a blow.  The
higher a monk's block counter, the better the monk can parry blows.
The block counter resets shortly after fights.
~

0 NINJA NINJAS~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
The powers of stealth and cunning make the ninja a supremly hated assassin.
Most would gladly kill you for fun let alone status.
Ninja's are masters of their surroundings.

#0[#7*#0]#n Discipline  -  Make more ninjas.
#0[#7*#0]#n Favour      -  This command is for inducting/outcasting & promoting.
#0[#7*#0]#n Ki          -  Used for powers. The more ki the quicker the ninja.
#0[#7*#0]#n Miktalk     -  Ninja only communication channel.
#0[#7*#0]#n Michi       -  Ninja rage-type power.
#0[#7*#0]#n Meditate    -  Regain health faster.
#0[#7*#0]#n Ninjagear   -  Command to get ninja equipment.
#0[#7*#0]#n Principles  -  Command to get ninja powers.
#0[#7*#0]#n Upkeep      -  This command shows what powers you currantly have.
#0[#7*#0]#n Belts       -  Belts are gained via train. (No Help: Find out yourself)

Also see help: #wPRINCIPLES#n
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 PRINCIPLE PRINCIPLES~
Principles are special powers that a sacred ninja learns,
for more information on these deadly powers, check the following helps:
Sora, Chikyu, and Ningenno. Those are the principles of the ninja powers.
~

0 SORA~

Sora - The Art of finding, observing, and locating principles.

Mitsukeru    :Locate-       The power to scry mobs, or foes.
Koryou       :Consider-     Read aura, learn more about your enemies.
Kakusu       :Hidden-       Enhanced Hide, which only ninjas can see you.
Uro-Uro      :Silent Walk-  Leaves no footprint shown behind.(Auto)
Kanzuite     :Awareness-    A sacred vision that sees all.
Bomuzite     :Sleep Gas-    A gas that makes your enemies go to sleep.
Mizotamouyo  :Shadowwalk-   Dissipate and reform at another's location.
~

0 CHIKYU~

Chikyu - The Art of Preperation for battle.

Tsuyoku   :Strength-      Ninja Toughness.(Auto)
Songai    :Damage-        Enhanced damage.(Auto)
Isogu     :Haste-         Adds two extra attacks.(Auto)
Tsuiseki  :Hunt-          Fast hunting.
Sakeru    :Sonic Speed-   Dodges more attacks.(Auto)
HaraKiri  :Blood Power-   Hurt yourself to gain power.
Orimasu   :Mending-       Regenerate at will.
Gunaya    :Net-           Entrap your foes with a spiritual net.
~

0 NINGENNO~
Ningenno - The Art of attacking and getting away from battle.

Tsume      :Claws-           Wrist worn claws or pure iron.
Hakunetsu  :First Strike-    Backstab before anyone has a chance.(Auto)
Mienaku    :Vanish-          Flee like smoke on the wind.
Shiroken   :Throwing Star-   Throw shiroken in combat.(Auto)
Dokuyaku   :Poison-          Your shiroken are dripping with poison.(Auto)
Circle     :Back Attack-     Move around your foe and attack from behind.
Trip       :Trip 'Em Up-     Trip your foe and send them sprawling.
~

0 HIGHLANDER HIGHLANDERS KENSAI~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Highlanders are skilled elite combatant fighters, they only need one thing,
a forged weapon. Within that weapon lies their true power, as being a highlander,
you have the gift of getting 1000 skill in all weapons. Armour is nothing to
you, spells are nothing, all that is needed is your forged weapon, the more
maxed out in slice you are the more hit/dam/ac you will gain.

#0[#7*#0]#n Forge       -  Makes different weapons.
#0[#7*#0]#n Hightalk    -  This is the Highlander only communication channel.
#0[#7*#0]#n Nightsight  -  Utilize the moon to see better.
#0[#7*#0]#n Shadowsight -  Look past the planer barriers.
#0[#7*#0]#n Truesight   -  Gives you Eyes of the Raven.
#0[#7*#0]#n Kwalk	-  Kensai command to travel.

Highlanders will now start to gain powers as they become closer to being 
the one. The more you cap, the more skills you'll have.
    Skill    -  Info                                        - Status
#0[#7*#0]#n Readaura   -  Lets you judge your enemy's powers.       - #w 5#n
#0[#7*#0]#n Sense      -  Lets you see where another Highlander is. - #w10#n
#0[#7*#0]#n Shield     -  Protects you from scry and readaura.      - #w10#n
#0[#7*#0]#n Stare      -  Helps prevent an opponent from fleeing.   - #w10#n
#0[#7*#0]#n Sixthsense -  Powerful senses, can sense intent.        - #w15#n

If you are a highlander you have the natural ability to train your stats
(wis,int,dex,con,str) to 25 which is maximum, only you as a highlander have
that ability. Also Highlanders will strike back with a riposte while wielding
a weapon in combat.

#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 WEREWOLF WEREWOLVES GAROU WOLF~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
At the beginning of things, Gaia - the world and the spirit that embodies it -
set all things in a balance that would maintain and encourage life. Near the
top of this chain of being was humanity, and above them were the Garou - the
sacred warriors of the spirit. They were appointed to be the crusaders against
the Wyrm, who spreads its cancer through the humans. They are the preservers
of the raw essence of life, of nature's diversity and purity. They are the
Earth's immune system, fighting the disease of the Wyrm. They are the
werewolves, and they fight and destroy the children of the Wyrm
(such as the Kindred) at every opportunity.

#0[#7*#0]#n Calm      - Lets you shift back from Crinos form.
#0[#7*#0]#n Claw      - Transforms target into a werewolf, but costs 10000 exp. 
#0[#7*#0]#n Favour    - This command is for inducting/outcasting & promoting.
#0[#7*#0]#n Gifts     - Lists the current totem powers you have at your control.
#0[#7*#0]#n Howl      - A special channel that only werewolves can understand.
#0[#7*#0]#n Introduce - Informs everyone in the room of your werewolf lineage.
#0[#7*#0]#n Rage      - This gets you into a fluster and makes you shift form.
#0[#7*#0]#n Train     - Specials in train include silver tolerance and gnosis.
#0[#7*#0]#n Tribe     - Shows information on other werewolves logged on.
#0[#7*#0]#n Upkeep    - This command shows what powers you currantly have.

see help: #wGIFTS#n, #wBREEDS#n, #wAUSPICE#n, #wTRIBES#n.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 GIFT GIFTS TOTEM TOTEMS~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
The Garou gains access to gifts through three distinct ways these are breed,
auspice and tribe. Gifts are powers, tricks, and skills that the Garou have
learned through their contact with the spirit world.

Garou can learn any gift up to 4 but can only raise a certain number of
them to 5. The amount a werewolf can get to 5 is based on 2 factors:
Age and Generation.
The max number of gifts ANY Werewolf can get to 5 is 15.

Breed                 Auspice               Tribe

Homid                 Ragabash              Black Furies
Metis                 Theurge               Children of Gaia
Lupus                 Philodox              Fianna
                      Galliard              Get of Fenris
                      Ahroun                Red Talons
                                            Shadow Lords
                                            Silent Striders
                                            Silver Fangs
                                            Stargazers
                                            Uktena
                                            Wendigo

see help: #wBREEDS#n, #wAUSPICE#n, #wTRIBES#n.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 BREED BREEDS~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
A werewolf's breed is their natural form. Breed gifts often originate 
in spirits who owe the breed a favour for some kindness or help in the
past.  

Homid : This is the human face of the Garou. When they walk amoung men. 
Lupus : The Garou's natural form is a wolf.
Metis : This is a result of doing what is forbidden. When two Garou 
        reproduce they produce metis. The natural form of the metis
        is the feared crinos form; the man wolf killing machine form.

Type help <breed name> for information on gifts attained from the
different breeds

see help: #wAUSPICE#n, #wTRIBES#n.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 HOMID HOMIDS~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
The Gifts of the Homid breed incorporate mankind's abilities and skills as
toolmakers and cultural beings. They also include the side that involves the
conquering of nature. Humans have great controll over their invironment and
these gifts embody that control.

The Gifts of the Homid breed are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Persuasion
         Syntax: persuasion(Automatic)
         Your very presence is enough to persuade your foes from attacking, while
         others may even help you
	
#0[#7**#0]#n    Staredown
	   Syntax: staredown <target>
         By staring into the eyes of an enemy, you can cause them to flee in
         terror.
         *Note that this gift may only be used in combat
	
#0[#7***#0]#n   Disquiet
         Syntax: disquiet <target>
         Your eyes glow red as you stare into the eyes of your opponent, causing
         them to become anxious. They have trouble concentrating, making it
         harder for them to deal with combat.
         *Note that this is a curse (-25 hit/dam) and that if you type disquiet
         without a target you will use it on yourself.
	
#0[#7****#0]#n  Reshape Object
         Syntax: reshape <object> <description>
         With this gift you can reshape an item into your heart's desire.
         *Note that if you have this power you should probably use it instead of
         wasting quest points on 'quest <object> <name/long/short>'
	
#0[#7*****#0]#n Cocoon
         Syntax: cocoon
         WIth this gift you can cause a thick, opaque epidermis to surround you.
         This 'cocoon' will help protect you in combat.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 METIS~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Metis are outcasts in Garou society.  However, unlike the other breeds metis
are born directly into werewolf society and raised within it. Because of this,
they have a stronger connection with many Garou allies.

The Gifts of the Metis breed are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Quills
         Syntax: quills
         With this Gift you can make your fur bristly and sharp, like the
         quills of a porcupine.

#0[#7**#0]#n    Burrow
         Syntax: burrow <target>
         With this gift you can burrow a tunnel through the earth to any
         other garou.

#0[#7***#0]#n   Eyes of the Cat
         Syntax: eyes
         This Gift allows the garou to see clearly in the dark. The Garou's
         eyes will glow a light green while this power is in affect.
	
#0[#7****#0]#n  Wither Limb
         Syntax: wither <target>
         This gift allows you to stare intently at someone and cause a random
         limb to wither and fall from their body.

#0[#7*****#0]#n Madness
         Syntax: Madness
         This gift allows you to induce madness in those surrounding you. It
         affects a random number of people in the room. Those affected will
         wander off in random directions.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 LUPUS~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Lupus Garou are those born from a werewolf and wolf. Lupus are born and raised
among the wolves. Being born among wolves and living wild, lupus have a hard
time adjusting the their human form. Garou of the lupus breed are very in sync
with thair innate insticts, and their gifts reflect this.

The Gifts of the Lupus breed are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Heightened Senses
         Syntax: heightened
         With this gift a Garou can vastly increase their senses, making
         things they did not even know were there become easily detectable.
	
#0[#7**#0]#n    Catfeet
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         This gift grants the garou the agility of a cat.

#0[#7***#0]#n   Gnaw
         Syntax: Gnaw
         The Garou's teeth are strengthened to the point that they can chew
         through just about anything.  This is especially helpful when tied
         up or restrained in some manner.

#0[#7****#0]#n  Elemental Gift
         Syntax: elementalgift <target>
         This gift allows the Garou to call upon the forces of Gaia. The
         target of this attack is annihilated by the primal forces of Gaia
         herself. This can be helpful as it can be used while in combat.

#0[#7*****#0]#n Song of the Great Beast
         Syntax: song
         By howling at the sky, the Garou may call one of the Great Beasts
         -- a dinosaur. This beast will follow the whim of the summoner.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 AUSPICE~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Ragabash : The new moon which is represented by the trickster.
Theurge  : The Garou spirtualists are most often Theurge.
Philodox : As the moon reaches half way these are the Garou judges who
           meditate between the different auspices.
Galliard : These are the song writers, the dancers and the loremasters.
Ahroun   : The full moon represents the height of Gaia's rage and is
           composed of Gaia's choosen warriors.

For information on the gifts associated with a particular auspice type
help <auspice name>

see help: #wTRIBES#n.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 RAGABASH~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Ragabash are the Garou tricksters. Ragabash gifts reflect their nature. The
Gifts of the New Moon involve stealth and thievery.

The Gifts of the Ragabash auspice are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Blur of the Milky Eye
         Syntax: blur
         With this Gift a werewolf is able to distort the perception of others.  
         This distortion makes the Garou appear as only a shimmering blur.
         Those who see this blur perceive it as glare or just blink and assume
         it was a trick of the light. Those with above normal senses will not
         be affected.
	
#0[#7**#0]#n    Scent of Running Water
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         This Gift allows Garou to completely mask their scent. This makes it
         virtually impossible for anyone to track them.

#0[#7***#0]#n   Violation
         Syntax: violation <target>
         With this gift a Garou becomes familiar with the hate and revulsion
         of others, and gains the ability to amplify these feelings. A victim
         of this power is so overwrought with emotions that they are unable to
         concentrate. This lack of concentration prevents the subject from
         casting any spells.

#0[#7****#0]#n  Luna's Blessing
         Syntax: lunasblessing
         The Garou may pray to Luna, asking for her assistance. Luna sends a
         beam of moonlight down to engulf the fortunate Garou, imbuing them
         with strength.
         *Note that this is a bless (50 hit/dam, save vs. spell -12).

#0[#7*****#0]#n Whelp's Body
         Syntax: whelpsbody <target>
         A Garou with this gift may place a horrible curse on a foe. The body
         of one affected by this curse will weaken and diminish in strength.
         *Note that this curse causes -3000 hp. It doesnt last long tho, the
         targets hp will restore halfway in a few ticks and fully in a few more.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 THEURGE~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Theurge are the Garou seers and have great insight into the spirit world and
those that dwell within.

The Gifts of the Theurge auspice are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Mother's Touch
         Syntax: motherstouch <target>
         Garou with this gift need only to lay their hands on someone to heal
         their wounds.  
         *Note that you cannot use this gift on yourself and that it heals
         around 500 hp per use.

#0[#7**#0]#n    Grasp the Beyond
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         With this Gift a Garou is able to manipulate objects in the spirit
         world, the garou may pick objects in the umbra from without or
         vise-versa.

#0[#7***#0]#n   Spirit Drain
         Syntax: spiritdrain <corpse>
         A Garou with with Gift is able to draw life-energy from that which
         has died. When a Garou drains a corpse, whatever life-energy remains
         is used to replenish the garou's own energy.
	
#0[#7****#0]#n  Feral Lobotomy
         Syntax: feral <target>
         With this gift you can deliver a devastating blow to your opponents
         forehead. This attack can become even more powerful when combined with
         the mystical gifts of the Uktena tribe.
	
#0[#7*****#0]#n The Malleable Spirit
         Syntax: malleable <object>
         Every object has a spirit that dwells within, with this gifts you can
         manipulate this spirit. By manipulating the spirit within a weapon you
         can increase its effectiveness.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 PHILODOX~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
The Philodox are the judges of Garou society. They mediate and help make
important decisions. Philodox gifts help them determine truth from lie, right
from wrong.

The Gifts of the Philodox auspice are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Resist Pain
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         Garou with this gift are able to ignore their pain. They can continue
         to fuction normally.
	
#0[#7**#0]#n    King of the Beasts
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         Beasts of legends past grant some of their strength to Garou
         possessing this gift.
	
#0[#7***#0]#n   Strength of Purpose
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         This gift grants a garou the ability to gain extra resolve in times of
         need. When Garou with this gift need it most they can gain extra
         strength to survive.
	
#0[#7****#0]#n  Weak Arm
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         Garou with this gift learn to exploit the weaknesses of others. They
         learn to watch others and perceive their strengths and failings.
         Using this knowledge the Garou can do more damage to an opponent.
	
#0[#7*****#0]#n Wall of Granite
         Syntax: granite
         A Garou with this is more in touch with the elementals of earth. With
         this gift a Garou can call upon these elementals for a little extra
         protection, a wall of granite to surround their body and protect them.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 GALLIARD~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
The Galliard are the song writers and sory tellers in Garou society.  

The Gifts of the Galliard auspice are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Call of The Wyld
         Syntax: wyld
         In times of great need Garou with this gift may howl for assistance.
         All Garou will hear this call, they will instinctively where to find
         the caller and who they are fighting.

#0[#7**#0]#n    Klaive
         Syntax: klaive
         Garou with this gift may call a great weapon from ancient times into
         existence, the Klaive. This klaive will not be as powerful as those of
         long ago, a lesser klaive as it were. Being a mystical weapon, this
         dagger may even be wielded in crinos form.
         *Note, it will cost you 85 primal energy to create a lesser klaive.
	
#0[#7***#0]#n   Song of Rage
         Syntax: ragesong <target>
         A Garou with this gift can unleash the beast in others. Other Garou
         will transform into crinos form, vamps will frenzy, and everyone else
         will go berserk.
	
#0[#7****#0]#n  Eye of the Cobra
         Syntax: eyeofcobra <target>
         Garou with this gift can put almost anyone into a trance-like state.  
         Once in this trance, the target is powerless and at the whim of the user.
	
#0[#7*****#0]#n Bridge Walker
         Syntax: bridge <target>
         A Garou with this gift is able to create minor Moon Bridges. With these
         Bridges you can appear behind someone and attack them from behind.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 AHROUN~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Ahroun are warriors through and through. They are the most war-like and full
of rage. Ahroun gifts personify the their true nature.

The Gifts of the Ahroun auspice are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Inspiration
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         Garou with this gift are able to gain inspiration from all around them.
         Being inspired, they perform better in combat.

#0[#7**#0]#n    Razor Claws
         Syntax: razorclaws
         Garou with this gift may hone their claws to razor sharpness.
	
#0[#7***#0]#n   Heart of Fury
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         Garou with this gift can increase the potency of their rage, making
         them hit harder.

#0[#7****#0]#n  Clenched Jaw
         Syntax: clenched
         Garou with this gift can clamp their jaw on their opponents neck with
         a grip of steal. Once an opponent is caught in a Garou's clenched jaw,
         they cannot flee.

#0[#7*****#0]#n Stoking Fury's Furnace
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         A Garou with this gift is more in touch, more familiar with his rage.
         This familiarity allows the Garou to become stronger and hit harder
         than others.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 TRIBE TRIBES~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Each tribe has its own talents and special powers. Tribe Gifts are passed down
through generations. Most tribal Gifts originate with that tribe's totem spirit
or an allied spirit.

	       +-+-+-+-+-+-+   +-+-+   +-+-+-+   +-+-+-+-+-+
	       |T|r|i|b|e|s|   |o|f|   |t|h|e|   |G|a|r|o|u|
	       +-+-+-+-+-+-+   +-+-+   +-+-+-+   +-+-+-+-+-+


           Black Furies       Children of Gaia       Fianna

           Get of Fenris      Red Talons             Shadow Lords

           Silent Striders    Silver Fangs           Stargazers

           Uktena             Wendigo              

For information on each tribe's Gifts, type help <tribe>. 
#P=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=#n
~

0 BLACKFURIES 'BLACK FURIES'~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
The gifts of the Black Furies tribe reflect their protection of the Wyld.
Black Furies' gifts also embody a woman's pain and turn it onto their foes.

The Gifts of the Black Furies tribe are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Coup De Grace
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         Garou with this gift learn to study their opponent. When Garou with
         this gift attack, they first study their foe, learning where is best
         to hit. This knowledge allows the Garou to do a lot more damage on
         the first hit.
	
#0[#7**#0]#n    Visceral Agony
         Syntax: visceral
         This gift allows Garou to coat their claws with a poisonus black venom.
	
#0[#7***#0]#n   Body Wrack
         Syntax: bodywrack
         With this gift a Garou can focus gnosis on an opponent and cause them
         immense pain. This gift become more powerful as you learn more of the
         Black Furies ways.
	
#0[#7****#0]#n  Wasp Talons
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         With this gift Garou may literally hurl their claws at their foe.
	
#0[#7*****#0]#n Curse of Aeolus
         Syntax: aeolus
         Garou with this gift can fill a room with an eerie, chilling fog.
         This fog blinds the Garou's opponent and allows the Garou to escape
         from combat.
         *Note, stops all fights in the room.
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 SILVER SILVERFANGS 'SILVER FANGS'~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Silver Fangs is an ancient tribe of aristocrats. The once noble Silver Fang
tribe is on the verge of decay. Inbreeding and sickness has taken its toll.
They remain the leaders of the Garou, commanding Gaia's will, but for how long
is anyones guess.

The Gifts of the Silver Fangs tribe are as follows:

#0[#7*#0]#n     Lambent Flame
         Syntax: lambent
         With this gift Garou have the power to ignite a silvery glow around
         their body. This light blinds all within the room.

#0[#7**#0]#n    Silver Claws
         Syntax: (Automatic)
         When a Garou learns this gift their claws turn into silver. This
         makes them do extra damage to other werewolves.

#0[#7***#0]#n   Mindblock
         Syntax: mindblock
         Garou with this gift may raise a psychic shield. This shield blocks
         mental powers.
         *Note, immune to scry and readaura.

#0[#7****#0]#n  Luna's Avenger
         Syntax: lunasavenger
         Garou with this gift may cause their body to become imbued with
         silver, causing increased damage against other werewolves.

#0[#7*****#0]#n Paws of the Newborn Cub
         Syntax: paws <target>
         With this gift a Garou may cause a foe's body to shrink and weaken.
         *Note, this is a curse (-damcap).
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 REDTALONS 'RED TALONS'~
