0 PRIMAL~

Primal energy is the ultimate form of energy in the multiverse, the one 
from which all other energies are derived.  Unfortunately, unlike mana, 
primal energy is only one use, and is generally used for very powerful 
spells, such as 'voodoo' (which uses 5 points) and 'quest' (which uses 
between 1 and 50 points).
~

0 AVATAR~
#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
Training AVATAR meants that you are ready to join the Player killing fray.
Avatar has some advantages these are:

 #0[#7*#0]#n You dont get killed by mobs.
 #0[#7*#0]#n You dont have to eat or drink.
 #0[#7*#0]#n You can be classed.

Disadvantages of training Avatar:

 #0[#7*#0]#n You can be pkilled.

#0-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-#n
~

0 NEWBIE~
A newbie is a player that is under 10 hours with no class or status. 
If you cap a player under 10 hours you will automatically be paradoxed,
and the newbie will be restored and the decap will not work on him. 
However if the newbie decides to get status he is fair game.

Note classed people under 10 hours with no status are NOT considered
newbies with regards to decapping or bonus exp.

Newbies get *3 exp for the first 10 hours regardless of if they are classed.
~

